# Protect scanner / timer arming (frozen)

The killscan + ambient notice timer arming path is working after hard in-game
debugging (load hooks, PlayerCombat quest start, boot re-arm). **Do not modify
it unless the user explicitly asks.**

## Frozen surface

- `ArmRuntimeLoops`, `ScheduleBootArm`, `EnsurePlayerCombatQuest`
- `StartKillScanLoop` / `OnTimer` killscan branch (re-arm **before** tick body)
- `HandleGameResume` / `HandlePlayerLoadFromAlias` / alias `OnPlayerLoadGame`
- Main `OnInit` / `OnQuestInit` arming calls into the above

## Allowed nearby work

- Filter / toast / fixation / line-bank changes that do **not** edit arming
- Additive calls **after** proven ambient speak (e.g. `TickLookFixation`)

## Not allowed without permission

- “Cleanup” or reorder of boot/load arming
- Removing `TIMER_BOOT_ARM`, PlayerCombat start, or load re-register
- Putting risky natives back on the killscan hot path before re-arm
